Our Story

Taiwanese comfort,
crafted with care.

Hoja Lamb Clay Pot & Stir-fry brings the warmth and energy of Taiwan's night-market eateries to Richmond Hill. We specialize in slow-simmered lamb hot pots and vibrant Taiwanese stir-fry classics — dishes designed for sharing, savoring, and enjoying with good company.

Our kitchen draws from generations of Taiwanese culinary tradition, combining hearty clay-pot broths with street-food flavors that have made us a favorite among diners across the Greater Toronto Area. With a perfect 100/100 health score, we're proud to serve food you can feel good about.

The Experience

Where every meal
feels like a celebration.

Step into Hoja and you're transported to the lively energy of a Taiwanese night market. Our informal, warm atmosphere is built around the joy of shared dining — pull up a chair, order a hot pot, and enjoy the company.

Our menu reflects the growing popularity of Taiwanese comfort cuisine within the Greater Toronto Area, with dishes designed for group enjoyment and pairing with tea or light beverages.

🫕

Clay Pot Mastery

Slow-simmered broths that develop deep, layered flavors over hours of careful cooking.

🔥

Bold & Vibrant

A celebration of spice, texture, and aroma — street-food energy on every plate.

🍶

Pair & Share

Dishes designed for the table — pair your meal with tea or a light drink.

🌙

Night Market Vibes

A casual, lively setting that captures the spirit of Taiwan's beloved street-food culture.
